# s3-bagit configuration
#
# Credential sources are checked in this order:
#   1. $S3CMD_CONFIG     (explicit path to an s3cmd INI file)
#   2. ~/.s3cfg          (s3cmd's default config location)
#   3. boto3 default chain (~/.aws/credentials, AWS_* env vars,
#                          IAM role, AWS SSO, …)
# Paths 1 and 2 include the endpoint in the s3cmd file. Path 3 reads
# the endpoint from $S3_ENDPOINT_URL (or talks to AWS S3 by default).
#
# If nothing resolves, s3-bagit exits non-zero with a message naming
# each option.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option A — s3cmd config: if you already have ~/.s3cfg set up against
# your S3 endpoint, s3-bagit will pick it up automatically — nothing
# to configure here. To point at a non-default file:
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# S3CMD_CONFIG=/Users/you/.s3cfg-alt

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option B — boto3 / AWS credentials. For plain AWS S3, the standard
# AWS env vars or ~/.aws/credentials are enough. For a non-AWS S3-compatible
# endpoint, also set $S3_ENDPOINT_URL.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=...
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=...
# S3_ENDPOINT_URL=https://s3.example.com
